          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The  target   consisted  of  a  parallel - sided  cell",
                " containing a  uniform  layer of purified water 0.4 mm",
                " thick.  The cell walls of 12 micron  thick  tensioned",
                " mylar  were glued on to aluminium frames separated by",
                " a 0.4 mm spacer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three element dE-dE-E telescope."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " CsI(Tl)- and CsI-cristalls."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In  the  first  stage  of  the data-reduction process,",
                " proton events were separated from electrons and other",
                " particles   using   E-dE  information  from  detector",
                " telescope.  The proton energy  measured  at  the  CsI",
                " detector  was then corrected for energy losses in the",
                " target and dE-elements and combined with the emission",
                " angle  theta-p  and photon energy Eg to determine the",
                " missing energy. The missing energy was used to obtain",
                " the  excitation  energy  E-exc which is equal missing",
                " energy less the separation  energy  for  ground-state",
                " reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors are given."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The    systematic    uncertainty    due    to",
                " uncertainties in the solid angle,  target thickness,",
                " tagging  efficiency  and  dead-time  corrections  is",
                " estimated to be less than 6 %."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Angular  distributions  within the  range 25 - 125 deg",
                " are presented  for  the O-16(g,p) reaction populating",
                " low-lying states in N-15 at Eg = 60 and 72 MeV. These",
                " photon  energy values are the average values for 57 -",
                " 63 MeV and 68 - 76 MeV ranges. Comparison of the data",
                " with  self-consistent  Hartree-Fock  RPA calculations",
                " shows the importance of  meson-exchange  currents  in",
                " the photon-absorption."
              ]
            }
          ],
